Cluster life cycle management is a challenging task and Cluster API promises to  simplify provisioning, upgrading, and operating multiple Kubernetes clusters. With the growing adoption of CAPI in recent times, are you also looking into writing your own CAPI provider for your cloud?  This talk will walk you through the basics of Cluster API, to getting started on CAPI provider implementation, to building bare essentials like CSI & CPI, to how common problems like multi-tenancy, user quota management, networking constraints can be solved in a strong multitenant environments with Enterprise customers. Come and learn from the maintainers of another Cluster API provider on our journey moving from handcrafted Kubernetes cluster life cycle management to CAPI based lcm.
